raw_data.title: Program/Contract Manager
raw_data.description: Manages all facets of security systems program and contracts, ensuring compliance with government and company security policies and procedures. Obtains required licenses and registrations for product manufacturer, state and/or federal government regulations to successfully initiate, implement, and finalize security services (installation, repair, and/or maintenance) specified in the contract. Ensures that contractual obligations are met. Develops and implements security procedures in coordination with government agencies and management personnel. Monitors and conducts security briefings and security education programs. Ensures that proper tests are conducted for Quality Assurance. Maintains liaison with outside agencies and keeps upper management informed of all security activities. Manages and coordinates assignments, scheduling, and training for staff. Responsible for making sure staff performance meets or exceeds expectations, and all applicable standards and guidelines are adhered to. Makes on-site visits as necessary.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 5 additional years' experience can substitute for degree

labor_categories.years_experience: 5 additional years' experience can substitute for degree

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Oversees security system project, managing all coordination of security system installation, repair, and maintenance. Provides regular reports on project progress to Security Systems Program/Contract Manager. Responsible for ensuring that all staff successfully perform work, adhere to all required standards, and follow all required guidelines specified by government agencies and management personnel. Provides weekly and monthly safety briefings. Performs other responsibilities of Security Systems Specialist as needed.

raw_data.title: Systems Engineer I
raw_data.description: Designs and installs security systems, keeping in accordance with manufacturer’s specifications, Government customer standards, and all state and/or federal government regulations. Modifies new and existing security systems as needed. Works in conjunction with CAD Operator/Designer to draft, design, modify, and finalize security system plans.

raw_data.title: QA Specialist
raw_data.description: Provides evidence needed (from witnessing the testing to performing audit testing) to establish confidence among all concerned that security systems and testing performed meet the contract specifications and are in complete code compliance for the work being performed. The Security Systems QA Specialist is responsible for periodic inspection and documentation of products and services to satisfy given requirements for content and quality. Ensures that services and products provided meet contract specifications, manufacturer’s specifications, Government customer standards, and all state and/or Federal Government regulations.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 4 additional years' experience can substitute for degree

labor_categories.years_experience: 4 additional years' experience can substitute for degree

raw_data.title: Computer Aided Design (CAD)
raw_data.description: Performs drafting duties in accordance with Security Systems Engineer and Security Systems Program/Contract Manager. Utilizes CAD to draft hand-drawn security systems layouts and wiring as needed. Modifies existing drawings as required. Ensures that all drawings meet standards of Authority Having Jurisdiction (AHJ) and all other applicable guidelines. Purchases electrical permits, prepares submittals and O&M Manuals, and reviews all testing paperwork for accuracy before projects are finalized.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: CAD cert or 2 additional years' experience can substitue for degree

labor_categories.years_experience: CAD cert or 2 additional years' experience can substitue for degree

raw_data.title: Security Systems Specialist I
raw_data.description: Installs all Electronic Security System and Integrated Commercial Intrusion Detection Systems (ICIDS) related audio, video, security, CCTV, and life-safety equipment. Installs all cable and connectors related to the equipment. Inspects, tests, maintains, and repairs installed security systems in accordance with manufacturer’s specifications and state and/or federal governmental standards. Fixes or replaces any defective components found. Tests initiating, notification and monitoring appliances and their method of transmission to the central station, and makes needed repairs. Applies knowledge of security systems as appropriate. Monitors security system and responds to security-related situations as necessary.
